        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 4 at 1:03AM CDT until April 4 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>SVRMAF

The National Weather Service in Midland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Scurry County in western Texas...
Mitchell County in western Texas...

* Until 200 AM CDT.

* At 103 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles southeast
of Forsan, or 15 miles northwest of Sterling City, moving northeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Colorado City Airport, Inadale, Hermleigh, Loraine, Lake Colorado
City, Champion Creek Reservoir, Westbrook, Lake Colorado City State
Park, Buford, and Colorado City.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 207 and 228.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
